column2: Families with Children Entering Homeless Shelters (Legacy Data)
The number of families entering Department of Homeless Services family shelters. Community District data represent family's last Community District of residence.

New York City Department of Homeless Services, unpublished data (Fiscal Years 2005-2015); Mayor's Management Report, Department of Homeless Services (Fiscal Years 2016-2021); Retrieved from https://www1.nyc.gov/site/operations/performance/mmr.page

These data are no longer reported. In 2016, CCC stopped receiving these data on the Community District level. Totals for the city are reported from the Mayors Management Report. Community District level data on Families in Shelter are available in our new indicator, Families with Children in Homeless Shelters. 

Rate refer to the number of families entering Department of Homeless Services family shelters per 1,000 households in that district.
